{
  "title": "NAIC President Jon Godfread on AI in Insurance",
  "body": "<html><body><div class=\"ContentPanel\" id=\"mainContentWrapper\">\n<div data-height-offset=\"true\" id=\"masterMainBreadcrumb\"></div>\n<div id=\"ctl01_UserMessagesUpdatePanel\">\n</div>\n\n<div id=\"ctl01_TemplateBody_PublishUpdatePanel\">\n</div><div id=\"ctl01_TemplateBody_WebPartManager1___Drag\" style=\"display:none;position:absolute;z-index:32000;filter:alpha(opacity=75);\">\n</div>\n<div>\n<div class=\"row\">\n<div class=\"col-sm-12\">\n<div class=\"ContentItemContainer\">\n<div class=\"WebPartZone\" id=\"WebPartZone1_Page1\">\n<div class=\"iMIS-WebPart\">\n<div class=\"ContentItemContainer\" id=\"ste_container_ciNewContentHtml4_8011555a00f841a4983d8d67ea33b88a\"><div id=\"ctl01_TemplateBody_WebPartManager1_gwpciNewContentHtml4_8011555a00f841a4983d8d67ea33b88a_ciNewContentHtml4_8011555a00f841a4983d8d67ea33b88a_Panel_NewContentHtml4\">\n<h2>NAIC President Jon Godfread on AI in Insurance </h2>\n</div></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div id=\"ctl01_TemplateBody_ContentPage1_downloadContainer\" style=\"display:none;\">\n<input id=\"ctl01_TemplateBody_ContentPage1_HiddenDownloadPathField\" name=\"ctl01$TemplateBody$ContentPage1$HiddenDownloadPathField\" type=\"hidden\"/><input id=\"ctl01_TemplateBody_ContentPage1_downloadButton\" name=\"ctl01$TemplateBody$ContentPage1$downloadButton\" style=\"display:none\" type=\"submit\" value=\"Download Path\"/>\n</div></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"row\">\n<div class=\"col-sm-8\">\n<div class=\"ContentItemContainer\">\n<div class=\"WebPartZone\" id=\"WebPartZone2_Page1\">\n<div class=\"iMIS-WebPart\">\n<div class=\"ContentItemContainer\" id=\"ste_container_ciNewContentHtml2_23bc8198cd3f445bba39d9525872c94c\"><div id=\"ctl01_TemplateBody_WebPartManager1_gwpciNewContentHtml2_23bc8198cd3f445bba39d9525872c94c_ciNewContentHtml2_23bc8198cd3f445bba39d9525872c94c_Panel_NewContentHtml2\">\n<h4>Bridging the Gaps Between Innovation and Protection</h4><p>In a recent conversation with Frank Paul Tomasello, J.D., Executive Director of The Institutes Griffith Foundation, NAIC President Jon Godfread discussed how artificial intelligence (AI) could reshape the insurance industry. He emphasized the importance of closing protection gaps, maintaining affordability, and building consumer trust while adapting regulatory frameworks to new technologies.</p>\n</div></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div id=\"ctl01_TemplateBody_ContentPage2_downloadContainer\" style=\"display:none;\">\n<input id=\"ctl01_TemplateBody_ContentPage2_HiddenDownloadPathField\" name=\"ctl01$TemplateBody$ContentPage2$HiddenDownloadPathField\" type=\"hidden\"/><input id=\"ctl01_TemplateBody_ContentPage2_downloadButton\" name=\"ctl01$TemplateBody$ContentPage2$downloadButton\" style=\"display:none\" type=\"submit\" value=\"Download Path\"/>\n</div></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"col-sm-4\">\n<div class=\"ContentItemContainer\">\n<div class=\"WebPartZone\" id=\"WebPartZone3_Page1\">\n<div class=\"iMIS-WebPart\">\n<div class=\"ContentItemContainer\" id=\"ste_container_ciNewContentHtml3_197f7ac93155483eb7083ef069e15d76\"><div id=\"ctl01_TemplateBody_WebPartManager1_gwpciNewContentHtml3_197f7ac93155483eb7083ef069e15d76_ciNewContentHtml3_197f7ac93155483eb7083ef069e15d76_Panel_NewContentHtml3\">\n<a href=\"https://youtu.be/INeWbyzpA48?si=EnVxn6zjl4KQ3yu0\" target=\"_blank\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/images/IASA/Insight%20Articles/Godfread-Video-interview-cover.png?version=E8C1B576\" style=\"width: 600px;\"/></a>\n</div></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div id=\"ctl01_TemplateBody_ContentPage3_downloadContainer\" style=\"display:none;\">\n<input id=\"ctl01_TemplateBody_ContentPage3_HiddenDownloadPathField\" name=\"ctl01$TemplateBody$ContentPage3$HiddenDownloadPathField\" type=\"hidden\"/><input id=\"ctl01_TemplateBody_ContentPage3_downloadButton\" name=\"ctl01$TemplateBody$ContentPage3$downloadButton\" style=\"display:none\" type=\"submit\" value=\"Download Path\"/>\n</div></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"row\">\n<div class=\"col-sm-12\">\n<div class=\"ContentItemContainer\">\n<div class=\"WebPartZone\" id=\"WebPartZone4_Page1\">\n<div class=\"iMIS-WebPart\">\n<div class=\"ContentItemContainer\" id=\"ste_container_ciNewContentHtml1_ddf241d590fe4510a1e6d114625c2de1\"><div id=\"ctl01_TemplateBody_WebPartManager1_gwpciNewContentHtml1_ddf241d590fe4510a1e6d114625c2de1_ciNewContentHtml1_ddf241d590fe4510a1e6d114625c2de1_Panel_NewContentHtml1\">\n<h3 data-end=\"755\" data-start=\"694\">Why Protection Gaps Matter in Today’s Insurance Climate</h3>\n<p data-end=\"948\" data-start=\"756\">Affordability and access to insurance remain pressing challenges. Inflation and severe weather are driving higher premiums, making it harder for some consumers to maintain adequate coverage.</p>\n<p data-end=\"1126\" data-start=\"950\">Godfread noted that data collection and the United States’ state-based regulatory system are key tools for maintaining industry solvency and ensuring consumers are protected.</p>\n<h3 data-end=\"1187\" data-start=\"1128\">NAIC’s Role in Collaborative, Market-Based Regulation</h3>\n<p data-end=\"1467\" data-start=\"1188\">Representing commissioners from 56 jurisdictions, the NAIC provides a platform for collaboration and knowledge-sharing. Successful initiatives like <em data-end=\"1362\" data-start=\"1336\">Strengthen Alabama Homes</em> demonstrate how resiliency programs can reduce risk for homeowners and help keep insurance affordable.</p>\n<h3 data-end=\"1505\" data-start=\"1469\">The Promise of AI in Insurance</h3>\n<p data-end=\"1639\" data-start=\"1506\">Godfread expressed optimism about AI’s potential to streamline processes and improve the customer experience. Applications include:</p>\n<ul data-end=\"1764\" data-start=\"1640\">\n<li data-end=\"1695\" data-start=\"1640\">\n<p data-end=\"1695\" data-start=\"1642\"><strong data-end=\"1673\" data-start=\"1642\">Expedited claims processing</strong> for faster payouts.</p>\n</li>\n<li data-end=\"1764\" data-start=\"1696\">\n<p data-end=\"1764\" data-start=\"1698\"><strong data-end=\"1719\" data-start=\"1698\">Tailored policies</strong> that better fit individual consumer needs.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p data-end=\"1954\" data-start=\"1766\">At the same time, he stressed that AI adoption must be careful and deliberate to address potential challenges such as underwriting bias, privacy concerns, and maintaining consumer trust.</p>\n<h3 data-end=\"2004\" data-start=\"1956\">Adapting Regulation Without Overhauling It</h3>\n<p data-end=\"2246\" data-start=\"2005\">Rather than rewriting existing laws from scratch, Godfread supports adapting current regulatory frameworks to integrate new technologies like AI. This approach aims to balance innovation with the protections already in place for consumers.</p>\n<h3 data-end=\"2267\" data-start=\"2248\">Looking Ahead</h3>\n<p data-end=\"2553\" data-start=\"2268\">As AI becomes more prevalent in the insurance industry, the focus will remain on addressing privacy, fairness, and transparency. For regulators, insurers, and policyholders alike, the goal is to ensure that innovation strengthens—not undermines—the foundation of consumer protection.</p>\n<p data-end=\"2645\" data-start=\"2555\"><strong data-end=\"2586\" data-start=\"2558\">Watch the full interview</strong> on <a href=\"https://youtu.be/INeWbyzpA48?si=aN5GqXZZOU9pnxrA\" target=\"_blank\">YouTube</a> to hear Jon Godfread’s complete remarks.</p>\n<p><a class=\"btn TextButton PrimaryButton\" href=\"https://youtu.be/INeWbyzpA48?si=EnVxn6zjl4KQ3yu0\" target=\"_blank\">Watch The Interview</a></p>\n<p>This video interview with NAIC President Jon Godfread was posted on YouTube by The Griffith Insurance Education Foundation. </p>\n</div></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div id=\"ctl01_TemplateBody_ContentPage4_downloadContainer\" style=\"display:none;\">\n<input id=\"ctl01_TemplateBody_ContentPage4_HiddenDownloadPathField\" name=\"ctl01$TemplateBody$ContentPage4$HiddenDownloadPathField\" type=\"hidden\"/><input id=\"ctl01_TemplateBody_ContentPage4_downloadButton\" name=\"ctl01$TemplateBody$ContentPage4$downloadButton\" style=\"display:none\" type=\"submit\" value=\"Download Path\"/>\n</div></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div></body></html>",
